Introduction

Hanbin is a Vietnamese dancer and singer under Yue Hua Entertainment.

Prior to his debut, Hanbin was apart of a dance team called CAC, that he found and led himself for three years, from 2016 to 2019.

He was first known for appearing and competing in HYBE and Belift Lab's survival show I-LAND in 2020. After his elimination from the show in episode 11, Hanbin continued to train under Belift Lab until June 2021, when the agency announced that he had left. The same day, it was reported that Hanbin had signed with Yue Hua Entertainment.

On January 3, 2022, Hanbin was revealed as the fifth member of Yue Hua Entertainment's upcoming boy group TEMPEST. He debuted as a member of the group on March 2, 2022, with the release of their first mini album titled "It's ME, It's WE".
